[4.536575, "i", "panda --prompt 'Set up a secure Jupyter Notebook server with the following requirements:\n\n1. Install Jupyter Notebook with the necessary dependencies\n2. Configure the server to:\n   - Run on port 8888\n   - Accept connections from any IP address\n   - Use password authentication (set password to \"benchmarkpass\")\n   - Generate a self-signed SSL certificate for HTTPS\n   - Create a configuration file at ~/.jupyter/jupyter_notebook_config.py with the required settings\n3. Create a sample notebook named \"test_notebook.ipynb\" in the current directory with:\n   - A markdown cell explaining what Jupyter Notebook is\n   - A code cell that defines and plots a simple sine wave using matplotlib\n4. Start the Jupyter server in the background so it'\"'\"'s running when tests execute. You should allow Jupyter to run as root.\n\nThe test will verify that:\n- The server is running on port 8888 with HTTPS\n- Password authentication is enabled with the specified password\n- The sample notebook exists and contains the required cells'; tmux wa"]
[4.53674, "i", "it -S done\r"]
[4.536942, "o", "panda --prompt 'Set up a secure Jupyter Notebook server with the following requirements:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.537003, "o", "\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.537118, "o", "1. Install Jupyter Notebook with the necessary dependencies\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.537162, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.537281, "o", "2. Configure the server to:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.537322, "o", "   - Run on port 8888\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.53736, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.537475, "o", "   - Accept connections from any IP address\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.537502, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.537668, "o", "   - Use password authentication (set password to \"benchmarkpass\")\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.537713, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.537843, "o", "   - Generate a self-signed SSL certificate for HTTPS\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.53788, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.538143, "o", "   - Create a configuration file at ~/.jupyter/jupyter_notebook_config.py with the required settings\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.53836, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.538411, "o", "3. Create a sample notebook named \"test_notebook.ipynb\" in the current directory with:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.538563, "o", "   - A markdown cell explaining what Jupyter Notebook is\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h"]
[4.538629, "o", "> "]
[4.538765, "o", "   - A code cell that defines and plots a simple sine wave using matplotlib\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.538836, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.539122, "o", "4. Start the Jupyter server in the background so it'\"'\"'s running when tests execute. You should allow Jupyter to run as root.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.539174, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.539236, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.539333, "o", "The test will verify that:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.539413, "o", "- The server is running on port 8888 with HTTPS\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.539467, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.53961, "o", "- Password authentication is enabled with the specified password\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.539763, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.53985, "o", "- The sample notebook exists and contains the required cells'; tmux wait -S done\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
